p: Aiming to obtain new alkaloids, Aldulaimi and collaborators isolated from Alphonsea cylindrical King two novel isoquinoline alkaloids, namely, iraqiine (15) and kareemine (16) ( Figure 1). In vitro antioxidant activity was performed, and the results showed IC 50 values of 48.77 and 101.66 μg mL −1, respectively. In this same test, five additional known alkaloids were tested and among them, O-methylmoschatoline (144.15 μg/mL) was better than kareemine [ 41].
